update_floorpl...or_macro_place(25.10)  update_floorpl...or_macro_place(25.10)

Name
       update_floorplan_for_macro_place  - Enables you to update the floorplan
       before defining constraints for macros  with  the  set_macro_place_con-
       straint command

Syntax
        update_floorplan_for_macro_place

       [-help]

       [-init_rows]

       [-keep_fixed_insts {<inst1 inst2 ...>}]

       [-remove    {all   route_blockage   place_blockage   relative_floorplan
       power_domain insts_place  wire  boundary_constraint  physical_inst  drc
       PG_pin}]

       Enables  you  to  update  the floorplan before defining constraints for
       macros with the set_macro_place_constraint command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each update_floorplan_for_macro_place parameter.
              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man update_floorplan_for_macro_place

       -init_rows
              Creates core rows.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -keep_fixed_insts {<inst1 inst2 ...>}
              Keeps  the specified instances in the floorplan. It sets the in-
              stances which are not unplaced.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -remove {all route_blockage place_blockage relative_floorplan power_do-
       main insts_place wire boundary_constraint physical_inst drc PG_pin}
              Removes the specified objects from the floorplan.

              Data_type: enum_list, optional

Example
              * The following command initializes the core  rows  and  deletes
                the placement blockages from the floorplan:

                update_floorplan_for_macro_place       -init_rows      -remove
                place_blockage

